&amp; sp.
</emphasis>
, male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A67FF9BFF1CFACEEE53FA6F" blockId="24.[151,1436,1371,2008]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A67FF9BFF1CFACEED4DFAA7" bold="true" box="[199,260,1371,1396]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A67FF9BFEC8FACEED8BFAA7" bold="true" box="[275,450,1371,1396]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Measurements</emphasis>
. Overall length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFDA7FACEEF6DFAA0" box="[636,804,1371,1396]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.65" metricValueMax="4.79" metricValueMin="4.51" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="4.65" valueMax="4.79" valueMin="4.51">4.51–4.79 mm</quantity>
; crown length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFC16FAC9E83CFAA0" box="[973,1141,1372,1396]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" metricValueMax="4.4" metricValueMin="4.2" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="0.43" valueMax="0.44" valueMin="0.42">0.42–0.44 mm</quantity>
; crown length next to eye 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFF4CFAEAECB6FA44" box="[151,255,1407,1432]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5999999999999996" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="0.36">0.36 mm</quantity>
; pronotum length 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFE15FAEAEE7FFA44" box="[462,566,1407,1432]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.50 mm</quantity>
; head width 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFD1CFA15EF66FA44" box="[711,815,1408,1432]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.38" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="1.38">1.38 mm</quantity>
; pronotum width 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFC23FA15E8D7FA44" box="[1016,1182,1408,1432]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.075" metricValueMax="1.11" metricValueMin="1.04" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="mm" value="1.075" valueMax="1.11" valueMin="1.04">1.04–1.11 mm</quantity>
; ocellus diameter 28.0 µm; interocellar distance 70.0 µm.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A67FF9BFF1CFA52ED40F80B" blockId="24.[151,1436,1371,2008]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A67FF9BFF1CFA52ED4DFA33" bold="true" box="[199,260,1479,1504]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A67FF9BFECDFA52EDCDFA33" bold="true" box="[278,388,1479,1504]" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Genitalia</emphasis>
. Genital capsule short in lateral view, wide anterior apodeme, subgenital plate extending beyond posterior margin of pygofer lobe (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFD59FA7EEF6FF9D7" box="[642,806,1515,1540]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Figs 13a, 13b</figureCitation>
). Tergite X short, tubular, incised about half-way into genital capsule, ventrally with large membranous recess (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFCECF99AEFD2F9FB" box="[823,923,1551,1576]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13a</figureCitation>
). Subgenital plate slightly longer than wide (1.16–1.25 times longer than wide, n=2), basal and medial margins sub-parallel, posterior margin acutely angled to medial margin; macrosetae near apex, submarginal, fine setae subapically and laterally (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFB4BF9C2E8BAF9A3" box="[1168,1267,1623,1648]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13c</figureCitation>
). Pygofer lobe about half as wide as width across base of genital capsule, short (as long as basal length of genital capsule) (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFAB4F9EEEC8DF96B" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13b</figureCitation>
); lobe apex with sclerotized, acuminate ventroposteriad process. Aedeagus with shaft tubular, straight in dorsal view, curved in lateral view; dorsally with sclerotized ridge ending in subapical tooth; ventrally with subapical, paired short teeth; basally with large conical tooth-like process (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFC5AF972E86AF8D3" box="[897,1059,1767,1792]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Figs 13d, 13e</figureCitation>
); gonopore apical, membranous; dorsal apodeme in lateral view triangular, in dorsal view inverted Y-shaped, arms short, medially with longitudinal ridge (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFF3EF8BAED02F89B" box="[229,331,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13e</figureCitation>
); aedeagal paraphysis longer than shaft, tubular, distal third acanthoid (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFB78F8BAE943F89B" box="[1187,1290,1839,1864]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13d</figureCitation>
). Style with apophysis weakly sclerotized, curvate, narrowly acuminate, directed lateroposterially, smooth, with dorsomedial digitate process; lateral anterior arm narrow, elongate; medial anterior arm short, wide, apex curved dorsad (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFAB4F8E2EC8DF867" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">
Fig. 
<quantity id="4CBF9B047A67FF9BFF4CF809EC8DF867" box="[151,196,1948,1972]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="kg" metricValue="1.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="225" unit="g" value="13.0">13g</quantity>
</figureCitation>
); style extending about half-way into plate (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFD13F80EEF62F867" box="[712,811,1947,1972]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13c</figureCitation>
). Connective medially concave, arms short, triangular (
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A67FF9BFF44F82AECB4F80B" box="[159,253,1983,2008]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="24.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[151,1431,195,1209]" captionTargetId="figure@24.[151,1436,193,1222]" captionTargetPageId="24" captionText="FIGURE 13a–g. Discolopeus triacaenus n.gen. &amp; sp., male and female genitalia, line drawing. a. Genital capsule, dorsally; b. Genital capsule, laterally; c. Subgenital plate, ventrally; d, e. Aedeagus, laterally and dorsally respectively; f. Connective, dorsally; g. Style, dorsally." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626837/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="225">Fig. 13f</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BF836E17A66FF9AFF1CFF02ED14FF2B" blockId="25.[151,1437,151,645]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">
<emphasis id="B933EAF37A66FF9AFF1CFF02ED57FF63" bold="true" box="[199,286,151,176]" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown due to lack of suitable specimens. Specimen in 
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFC09FF02E878FF63" box="[978,1073,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Fig. 15c</figureCitation>
with same collection details as males but different colour pattern, female in 
<figureCitation id="137C2A647A66FF9AFD41FF29EEA5FF06" box="[666,748,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURE 15" captionStartId="27.[151,250,1867,1889]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,194,1845]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,193,1845]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 15a–i. Discolopeus gen.n. species, habitus, D. triacaenus sp.n. a. Holotype, male; b. Paratype, male, Ladismith; c, d, e. Nietgenaamd, female; dorsally, laterally and face, respectively; f. Ladismith, female; D. tetracaenus sp.n.; g. Beaufort West, male; h. Rust en Vrede, Oudtshoorn, male; i. Holotype, male, Willowmore." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2626841/files/figure.png" pageId="25" pageNumber="226">Figs 15</figureCitation>
d–f with similar colour pattern to that of male, but different collection details.
</paragraph>
